<paragraph id="92E955C9CACA9EE2F9DDF4D547BC7C64" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251">
Specimen examined and matches 
<taxonomicName id="1FE00237AA611F5B89637B88A5D2BD26" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Perlophiura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perlophiura profundissima" order="Ophiurida" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="profundissima">Perlophiura profundissima</taxonomicName>
Belyaev and Litvinova, 1972 (
<bibRefCitation id="5146A610C7A6CF42328A7322B7E644A5" author="Belyaev, G" journalOrPublisher="Otdel Biologicheskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251" pagination="5 - 20" title="New genera and species of deep-sea ophiuroidea. Moskovskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelej Prirody." volume="3" year="1972">Belyaev and Litvinova 1972</bibRefCitation>
) voucher material, NHM_257, disc 3.1mm in diameter (Fig. 23).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06A94D21CAECFC6ADB374735FCF8E654" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251">Genetic data for this taxa with new GenBank accession numbers are provided in Table 2</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4ADA16DA32F415D4463854BA9B3EDDFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D5EB15E3507E6ABDD2DD4B2E7783FA29" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="238F6805765CDF42863F0CFBB0242796" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251">
Forms a unique monophyletic clade distinct from other AB01 specimens. Morphologically agrees with 
<taxonomicName id="50F6D5D7664E13D9D9E1F5FFFD4D930E" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Perlophiura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perlophiura profundissima" order="Ophiurida" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="profundissima">Perlophiura profundissima</taxonomicName>
but no genetic data available from type locality or any location for this taxon but type locality appears to be North Pacific at abyssal depths (
<bibRefCitation id="647BC1E03412C25450BFCAF0D2BB9F98" author="Belyaev, G" journalOrPublisher="Otdel Biologicheskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="7251" pagination="5 - 20" title="New genera and species of deep-sea ophiuroidea. Moskovskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelej Prirody." volume="3" year="1972">Belyaev and Litvinova 1972</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
